# Airtable (optional) — if both PAT and base id are set, feedback syncs to Airtable
# and the Projects table is merged with the in-app registry. Use a base dedicated to
# this lab; the PAT is embedded in the Vite client bundle.
#
# Best practice: keep one row per (ProjectSlug + PaneId) in PaneTallies and one row per
# Slug in Projects — the app normalizes slugs to lowercase, merges duplicate tally rows
# on read, and creates missing built-in (e.g. isocourt) project rows on load.
#
# Create a base with these **table names and field names** (single-line text unless noted):
#
# 1) Projects
#    - Name  (text)
#    - Slug  (text)   — e.g. isocourt, must match code registry for merged rows
#    - Description  (long text) optional
#
# 2) PaneTallies
#    - ProjectSlug  (text)
#    - PaneId       (text)  — e.g. current-site, sketch-sf
#    - Likes        (number, default 0)
#    - Dislikes     (number, default 0)
#    (One record per project + pane; the app will create missing rows on first use.)
#
# 3) PaneComments
#    - ProjectSlug  (text)
#    - PaneId       (text)
#    - Text         (long text)
#
# 4) Experiments  (optional; for future “experiment catalog” in the app)
#    - ProjectSlug  (text)
#    - Title        (text)
#    - Kind         (text) optional
#    - Path         (text) optional
#    - Notes        (long text) optional
#
VITE_AIRTABLE_PAT=pat_xxxxxxxx
VITE_AIRTABLE_BASE_ID=appXXXXXXXX
# VITE_AIRTABLE_TABLE_PROJECTS=Projects
# VITE_AIRTABLE_TABLE_PANE_TALLIES=PaneTallies
# VITE_AIRTABLE_TABLE_PANE_COMMENTS=PaneComments
# VITE_AIRTABLE_TABLE_EXPERIMENTS=Experiments
